openmediavault-snapraid-aio (8.1) stable; urgency=low

  * Update bundled snapraid-aio-script to v3.4 stable release
  * Add email_notifications toggle: enable/disable native OMV email per config;
    sender and receiver are pulled read-only from OMV system notification
    settings and hidden in the form when the feature is off
  * Fix EMAIL_ADDRESS using sender instead of primaryemail from OMV email config
  * Add Docker remote management fields to datamodel: docker_remote,
    docker_user, docker_host_services, docker_delay
  * Fix APPRISE_URL rendered as Bash array in generated config file
  * Improve SnapRAID array selector: show array name (label) instead of raw
    config file path; resolve symlinks to stable UUID-based paths as stored
    value; hide the /etc/snapraid.conf legacy symlink
  * Fix Salt deploy exit code 1 when all AIO configs are deleted (add noop state)
  * Pre-fill schedule comment with "SnapRAID AIO <array name>" on first-time creation
  * Add Array name column to config list table
  * Fix email sender/receiver not populated when creating a new config
  * Disable Telegram and Discord integrations (superseded by Apprise)
  * Hardcode CHECK_UPDATES=0; updates ship with the package
  * Wire EMAIL_ADDRESS/FROM_EMAIL_ADDRESS from OMV system email config
  * Split UI threshold section into Sync thresholds, Scrub settings,
    and SnapRAID options sections
  * Add Remote Docker management section to config form
  * Add descriptive hints to fields that previously had none
  * Fix misleading labels: force_zero, spindown, snap_status_notify,
    apprise, apprise_email, execute_before_spindown, smart_log_notify
  * Fix confdb create script missing executable bit in git
  * Replace global enable toggle with per-config Schedule button on the
    datatable; each config gets its own cron entry via OMV's Cron RPC;
    cron_uuid stored per-config so the schedule round-trips correctly
  * Remove Settings page, Settings navigation entry, and global enable field
  * Fix scheduling: cron_uuid field added to per-config datamodel; getSchedule
    uses stored cron_uuid (blank form for new), setSchedule uses new-entry
    sentinel on first save and persists returned UUID back to config
  * Fix setSchedule missing validateMethodParams (uuid not validated before use)
  * Fix setConfig to load existing object before setAssoc to preserve cron_uuid
  * Fix deleteConfig: remove /etc/snapraid-aio-<uuid>.conf and linked cron entry
  * Fix Salt: query conf.service.snapraidaio.config directly via omv_conf.get
    to avoid parent model field validation; normalise single/list return value
  * Fix etc-snapraid-aio_conf.j2: replace invalid get_by_filter([]) calls for
    email config with omv_conf.get on conf.system.notification.email
  * Fix getSchedule crashing with XPath error: Cron::get does not accept
    the new-entry sentinel UUID; return a hardcoded default object directly
    when no cron entry exists yet, and also recover from stale cron_uuid by
    clearing it and falling back to the same default; setSchedule retries
    as a new entry when the stored cron_uuid is stale
  * Fix setSchedule XPath error on save: getSchedule now returns uuid as
    the config UUID (not the cron UUID) and carries cron_uuid as a separate
    field; hidden cron_uuid field added to schedule form so it round-trips
    back to setSchedule; setSchedule reads cron_uuid from params directly
  * Change default schedule to custom (userdefined) at midnight daily so
    users can adjust the time immediately without switching execution type
  * Fix schedule form: replace invalid 'userdefined' execution value with
    'exactly' (the correct value accepted by the Cron RPC)
  * Fix setSchedule: wrap time fields as single-element arrays before
    passing to Cron::set (required for 'exactly' execution type);
    flatten arrays back to scalars in getSchedule for the form selects
  * Fix setSchedule: add required everynminute/everynhour/everyndayofmonth
    boolean fields (always false) to satisfy Cron RPC schema validation
  * Fix setSchedule: unset cron_uuid from cronParams before Cron::set;
    it is not a field in conf.system.cron.job and causes a 500 error

 -- OpenMediaVault Plugin Developers <plugins@omv-extras.org>  Thu, 26 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

